Ask HN: Can I own an IP address and take it with me across providers?
text: We are providing a service to businesses whose customers are all running a firewall. The customers need to manually allow our services IP address in their firewall, which is something we want them to do only once upon onboarding. How can I get the most stable IP address for our reverse proxy that I will hopefully never have to give up?

title: The Seven Circles of Meeting Hell
Show HN: Synura – Video Project Management
text:
Hey everyone, we've been working on an app to help creators tell their stories with video and this morning we launched our MVP into free early access: https://www.synura.com/changelog/#2022-11-29. There's a link to an early access FAQ there where you can create an account.

For this iteration we focused on trying to help people just get organized - put all your video plans in one place, keep track of your assets, and maintain a list of to-dos, because this is something that we've heard a lot of people struggle with when launching their YouTube or TikTok channels. That said, our vision includes a lot more: https://www.synura.com/handbook/general/direction/

We're building in the open at https://gitlab.com/synura/ if you'd like to check out what we're up to in more detail. Either way, this is our very first iteration so it's quite modest but I'd still love to hear feedback on what we've built and where we're headed.
